%% TrustyAI Service Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant TAS as TAS Controller
    participant LMES as LMES Controller
    participant GORCH as GORCH Controller
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>+ oauth-proxy
    participant EvalPod as LMEval Pod<br/>+ driver sidecar
    participant Orchestrator as Guardrails Orchestrator<br/>+ detector + gateway
    participant ModelMesh as ModelMesh / KServe
    participant DB as Database<br/>(PostgreSQL/MySQL)
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over User,TrustyAI: Flow 1: TrustyAI Service Deployment
        User->>K8sAPI: Create TrustyAIService CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        K8sAPI->>TAS: Watch event (reconcile)
        TAS->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount, Service,<br/>Deployment, Route, PVC/DB config<br/>Auth: SA Token
        TAS->>K8sAPI: Patch InferenceService<br/>with Logger URL<br/>Auth: SA Token
        ModelMesh->>TrustyAI: Send predictions<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS (serving cert)
        User->>Route: Access TrustyAI metrics<br/>443/TCP HTTPS (reencrypt)
        Route->>TrustyAI: Forward request<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS OAuth proxy
        TrustyAI->>DB: Store/retrieve data<br/>JDBC, TLS optional<br/>Auth: username/password
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over User,EvalPod: Flow 2: LM Evaluation Job
        User->>K8sAPI: Create LMEvalJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        K8sAPI->>LMES: Watch event (reconcile)
        LMES->>K8sAPI: Create Pod<br/>Auth: SA Token
        LMES->>EvalPod: Pod exec (driver container)<br/>SPDY, TLS, SA Token
        EvalPod->>ModelMesh: Evaluate model<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (configurable)
        EvalPod-->>LMES: Status updates<br/>gRPC (plaintext)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 230)
        Note over User,Orchestrator: Flow 3: Guardrails Orchestration
        User->>K8sAPI: Create GuardrailsOrchestrator CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        K8sAPI->>GORCH: Watch event (reconcile)
        GORCH->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment, Service, Routes<br/>Auth: SA Token
        User->>Route: Send inference request<br/>443/TCP HTTPS (edge TLS)
        Route->>Orchestrator: Forward<br/>8033/TCP or 8090/TCP HTTP
        Orchestrator->>Orchestrator: Run detectors<br/>(built-in regex)
        Orchestrator->>ModelMesh: Forward to LLM<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (configurable)
        Orchestrator-->>Route: Response
        Route-->>User: Guardrailed response
    end
